11</label><citation citation-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Kosambi</surname><given-names>D</given-names></name></person-group><source>Ann Eugen</source><year>1944</year><volume>12</volume><fpage>172</fpage></citation></ref><ref id="R12"><label>12</label><citation citation-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Haldane</surname><given-names>JBS</given-names></name></person-group><source>J Genet</source><year>1919</year><volume>8</volume><fpage>299</fpage></citation></ref></ref-list></back><floats-wrap><fig id="F1" position="float"><label>Figure 1</label><caption><p>A snap shot of the database. The individual view table shows samples of searching result; (a) Marker trait information table (ex: 8_shr-2, seed of rice) by clicking a specific marker name in the upper area (b) Marker trait view table (ex: 97AS1872, RFLP-PCR image of Chinese cabbage)</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="97320630003061F1"/></fig></floats-wrap></article>